// ── Human Voice & Emotional Authenticity Layer ────────────────────────────────
// The patterns that make content feel written by a person who has opinions,
// emotions, and a history — not generated by a process.
//
// Each pattern is calibrated to a specific emotional register:
// - Vulnerability: earning trust by showing fallibility
// - Conviction: communicating certainty without arrogance
// - Frustration: expressing genuine irritation at systemic problems
// - Humor: self-deprecating, wry, never forced
// - Empathy: recognizing why people make the mistakes they make
// - Skepticism: healthy pushback that eventually resolves
// - Enthusiasm: real interest, not performance
// - Self-correction: mid-thought refinement that reads as intelligent
// - Self-interruption: creating urgency and forward pull
// - Asides: parenthetical depth that rewards close reading

